{"Title": "Search for the double-beta decay of 82Se to the excited states of 82Kr with NEMO-3", "Year": 2020, "Source": "Nucl. Phys. A", "Volume": "996", "Issue": null, "Art.No": null, "PageStart": null, "PageEnd": null, "CitedBy": 0, "DOI": "10.1016/j.nuclphysa.2020.121701", "Link": "https://www.scopus.com/inward/record.uri?partnerID=HzOxMe3b&scp=85078494158&origin=inward", "Abstract": "\u00a9 2020 Elsevier B.V.The double-beta decay of 82Se to the 01 + excited state of 82Kr has been studied with the NEMO-3 detector using 0.93 kg of enriched 82Se measured for 4.75 y, corresponding to an exposure of 4.42 kg\u22c5y. A dedicated analysis to reconstruct the \u03b3-rays has been performed to search for events in the 2e2\u03b3 channel. No evidence of a 2\u03bd\u03b2\u03b2 decay to the 01 + state has been observed and a limit of T1/2 2\u03bd(Se82,0gs +\u219201 +)>1.3\u00d71021y at 90% CL has been set. Concerning the 0\u03bd\u03b2\u03b2 decay to the 01 + state, a limit for this decay has been obtained with T1/2 0\u03bd(Se82,0gs +\u219201 +)>2.3\u00d71022y at 90% CL, independently from the 2\u03bd\u03b2\u03b2 decay process. These results are obtained for the first time with a tracko-calo detector, reconstructing every particle in the final state.", "AuthorKeywords": ["82Se", "Double beta decay", "Excited state", "Neutrino"], "IndexKeywords": null, "DocumentType": "Journal", "PublicationStage": null, "OpenAccess": 2, "EID": "2-s2.0-85078494158", "SubjectAreas": [["Nuclear and High Energy Physics", "PHYS", "3106"]], "AuthorData": {"57220759641": {"Name": "Arnold R.", "AuthorID": "57220759641", "AffiliationID": "60103368, 60025995", "AffiliationName": "IPHC, ULP, CNRS/IN2P3"}, "56219488600": {"Name": "Nowacki F.", "AuthorID": "56219488600", "AffiliationID": "60103368, 60025995", "AffiliationName": "IPHC, ULP, CNRS/IN2P3"}, "6602534247": {"Name": "Augier C.", "AuthorID": "6602534247", "AffiliationID": "60073296, 60106017, 60000383", "AffiliationName": "LAL, Univ Paris-Sud, CNRS/